The paper deals with the evaluation of learned multiagent strategies, which is a core topic in game theory and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes new algorithms for ranking agents in general-sum many-player games with noisy outcomes, which is a challenging problem in multiagent systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science > Computer Science and Game Theory), which is dedicated to the study of game theory in computer science. The paper also proposes new machine learning algorithms for ranking agents, which makes it relevant to cs.AI (Computer Science > Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Computer Science > Machine Learning). The paper deals with multiagent systems, which is a topic covered by cs.MA (Computer Science > Multiagent Systems). Finally, the paper proposes a new solution concept based on graph theory, which is relevant to cs.SI (Computer Science > Social and Information Networks).
